<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#000050"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#FFFFFF" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Jasmina</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I am a level 41 barbarian warrior.  My current stats are:<P>135 Strength<BR>140 Stamina<BR>106 Agility<BR>128 Dexterity<P>Before this, I was using Thulian Claw/Silvery 1hander combo for dual wield, and the Exec Axe for 2handed.  I recently obtained a EBW (awesome weapon) and use that instead of the claw.  However, I noticed that a Level 45 Ranger was hitting for 28+ consitantly with hers, and Im hitting for low 20's consistantly with it.  She had like 170 strength with her strength buff (I think thats what she said).  <P>Heres where I need help...I have equipped Golden BP Choker (7 Agi/Dex?), 2X BP rings (6 Agi/Dex) and 2 Saphire Plat Earings (4str/2int).  I can trade the 2 BP Rings for 2 FE Rings (5str/dex) and get 200pp out of it also.  So, I would go from this:<P>135 Strength<BR>140 Stamina<BR>106 Agility<BR>128 Dexterity<P>to this:<P>145 Strength<BR>140 Stamina<BR>94 Agility<BR>126 Dexterity<P>This would give me some extra damage on the top end, but reduce any effects given to me by the extra agility.  My plans are to use Dual Wield almost always, except in cases of damage shields where I use the Exec Axe.  I also plan to get either another EBW, or a Painbringer to replace the Silvery 1hander.<P>Any opinions?  Id like more strength, but is it worth it to sacrifice the agility?  Im not really worried about the 2 dex loss, but the 12 agility could hurt.<P>Opinions?  Im really stuck at what to do here.<P>Thanks,<P>Shaioshao Dreamlady<BR>Level 41 Warrior<BR>Tarew Marr<BR>Crimson Sky<P><BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Slaydar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I can't believe a level 41 warrior would use any of that junk 0AC player made stuff. Get some jagged bands, if you need STR that bad, try for a TBB. Also, a dented brass mask on your face gives +3str. Hero barcer is +10STr and has 9AC. Don't give up so much AC for dex/agil you are a tank, not a monk(ey).<P>------------------<BR>Slaydar Rabidwolf, Half-Elf warrior of Tunare, Veeshan<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Foozin</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">My opinion is get AGI / DEX over 100 and concentrate on AC / STR.  I'm a Troll Warrior who started with AGI 90 / DEX 77.  Wish I could roll over but....<P>Now my stats are:<P>STR 154<BR>STA 125<BR>AGI 102<BR>DEX 100<P>I'm wearing:<BR>Crafted armor except:<BR>Liz Cloak<BR>Grotesque Mask<BR>Skull Shaped Barbute<BR>Thick Leather Apron<BR>Bloodstained Mantle (getting crafted)<BR>2 Jagged Bands<BR>2 Electrum Saphire Earrings<BR>Golden Black Pearl Choker<P>AC is around 730 or so.  Well eventually replace the earrings with a Diamondine and Ivandyr's Hoop and the Apron with TBB.<P>Just one man's opinion.<P>------------------<BR>Foozin Biguglee<BR>37th level Troll Warrior<BR>Mithaniel Marr<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Slaydar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">You can get gold-topaz (3AC/8Dis) earings now for 30pp each. They are the poor-tank's earings. Why have stats at 100+, is this some silly "magic number" theory? Lose the lame BP choker, as long as your agil is 75+ you are fine. Pick up anything with AC on your neck, steel coller, coller of undead proctection, etc.<P>------------------<BR>Slaydar Rabidwolf, Half-Elf warrior of Tunare, Veeshan<P></FONT></TD></TR></TAB